<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-01T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="354" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.731/36: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Armour</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-01T19:00:00-04:00">March 1,
                                    1944—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>363. Reference your no. 598, March 1. If you deem it necessary you may
                            inform the All America Cables Company that you have been authorized by
                            the Department to request that all copies of Embassy’s cables be
                            returned to the Embassy to insure adequate protection and security.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>